CRITICAL GIT RULES:
- NEVER run git restore, git reset, or git checkout without explicit user confirmation
- When user says "push", run: git add . && git commit -m "..." && git push
- When user says "commit", run: git add . && git commit -m "..."
- ALWAYS show the exact git command you're about to run and wait for confirmation
- If uncertain about a git command, ASK the user first

DO NOT make assumptions about git operations. Always be explicit.